The M1 carbine is a lightweight, easy to use semi-automatic carbine that became astandard ﬁrearm for the U.S. military during World War II, the Korean War and the Vietnam War, and was produced in several variants. It was widely used by U.S. and foreign military, paramilitary and police forces, and has also been a popular civilian ﬁrearm. A total of over 6.5 million M1 carbines of various models were manufactured, making it the most produced small arm for the American military during World War II. Despite being designed by Winchester, the great majority of these were made by other companies : the largest producer was the Inland division of General Motors, but many others were made by contractors as diverse as IBM, the Underwood Typewriter Company, and the Rock-Ola jukebox company. title: For Trade:  Carter Lake gun show
postcontent:
My opinion, for what it is worth. If you enjoy the freedom of firearms ownership and the responsibility that goes along with it, this applies to you. 
I attended the gun show in Carter Lake recently and was incredibly disturbed to see people walking around drinking beer and other alcoholic beverages. While no harm came of the situation, don't you (firearms owners) think that we are already fighting an uphill battle against mainstream perception? I, personally, think that we should be doing everything possible not to draw any negative attention to ourselves and to firearms in general. If the media were to get ahold of pictures of people at a gun show drinking beer, what on earth do you think they would report?!?!  I would never want to be portrayed as anything other than responsible when it comes to firearms ownership. We as a group need to wake up and evaluate how we are viewed by non-firearms enthusiasts. We should be ever wary of the image we present. In this day and age, we need to constantly politic for our right to the 2nd amendment. Perception is everything when it comes to firearms and the people that don't like them, and I guarantee you that we will be forced to battle for our freedoms even harder if we are portrayed as beer drinking fools walking around trying to buy up our list of goods for a coming apocalypse. 
I value my right to own firearms as one of the most important freedoms I have in our country! Please join me in doing everything possible not to allow ourselves to look like idiots!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Brand New Unopened Hodgdon CFE223 Powder
postcontent:
This is the new powder Hodgdon just came out with that is supposed to be ideal for ARs. It is also supposed to eliminate copper fouling. According to Hodgdon's load data, it produces among the most impressive velocities for .223/5.56 and .308/7.62. From Hodgdon's website:
"Introduced in January 2012, this versatile spherical rifle propellant incorporates in its formula CFE, Copper Fouling Eraser. This ingredient, originally used in military propellant, greatly deters copper fouling. It contributes to longer periods of top accuracy with less barrel cleaning time. Being a spherical powder, metering is superbly accurate. CFE 223 yields top velocities in many cartridges such as the 204 Ruger, 223 Remington/5.56mm NATO, 22-250 Remington and the 308 Winchester/7.62mm NATO, plus many, many more. Match, Varmint and AR shooters will love this one!"

I bought this powder a while ago on a whim, and then realized it burns too slow for my M1A, which is much more picky than AR pattern rifles. It is brand new and unopened. I would sell for $20 or trade for another powder or reloading stuff. Just send me an offer. Cash price is firm.
